
Privacy Policy

We appreciate your interest in Tetra Block  Game. This Privacy Policy outlines the types of personal information we collect and receive from you while you are using our website, as well as our methods for using, sharing, and protecting that information.

By using Tetra Block  Game, you consent to the practices described in this Privacy Policy.

    Information Collection

We collect information in several ways, including but not limited to:

    Information You Provide to Us: When you register for an account, subscribe to our newsletter, submit a game for review, or interact with us through our customer service, we may collect information like your name, email address, and other relevant data.

    Automatically Collected Information: We may automatically collect certain information about the devices you use to access  Tetra Block  Game, like your IP address, browser type, operating system, the pages you visit, and the time and date of your visit.

    Information from Cookies: We use cookies to personalize your experience on our website, analyze our website traffic, and understand where our visitors are coming from.

    Use of Information

We may use the information collected to:

    Enhance and personalize your user experience on our site.
    Respond to your comments, questions, and customer service requests.
    Communicate with you about new games, services, offers, promotions, and updates.
    Monitor and analyze trends, usage, and activities in connection with our site.

    Information Sharing and Disclosure

We do not sell or rent your personal information to third parties for their marketing purposes without your explicit consent. We may share your personal information in the following circumstances:

    To fulfill a service to you; for example, if you choose to purchase a game through our website, we may share your personal information with payment processors.
    To comply with any court order, law, or legal process, including responding to any government or regulatory request.
    To protect the rights, property, or safety of us, our users, or others.

    Data Security

We take reasonable measures, including administrative, technical, and physical safeguards, to protect your information from loss, theft, misuse, unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, and destruction. However, no Internet or email transmission is ever fully secure or error-free, so you should take special care in deciding what information you send to us.

    Children's Privacy

Our website is not intended for children under 13 years of age, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we learn we have collected or received personal information from a child under 13 without verification of parental consent, we will delete that information.

    Changes to Our Privacy Policy

We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page. You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.

    Contact Us

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at: drmohamedalzamil81@gmail.com.
